excerpt: Busy market for traditional clothing, handicrafts, spices & perfumes, plus eateries & shisha cafes.
detail_description: Discover the vibrant atmosphere of Souq Waqif, a bustling market in Doha that offers a glimpse into traditional Arabian culture. Renovated to capture the essence of authentic souqs found in cities like Aleppo and Damascus, this open-air street market is filled with narrow alleys where merchants trade perfumes, handicrafts, jewelry, weavings, and silverware.
name: Souq Waqif

excerpt: Waterfront area with an amphitheater, museum & convention center, plus shops, eateries & a beach.
detail_description: Katara Cultural Village is a waterfront complex in Doha that offers a blend of leisure, entertainment, and shopping. It pays homage to Qatar's past with its design as a traditional village featuring sandstone-hued lanes, mosques, cafes, boutiques, and coffee shops. The village also includes a 5,000-seater amphitheater overlooking the ocean where live concerts and entertainment take place.
name: Katara Cultural Village

excerpt: Landmark Pei-designed museum opened in 2008, with displays tracing 1400 years of Islamic art.
detail_description: The Museum of Islamic Art (MIA) in Doha, Qatar is a renowned landmark designed by architect M. Pei and opened in 2008. The museum's exterior facade resembles a mosque and changes color throughout the day. Inside, visitors can explore 1400 years of Islamic art through displays of glassware, ceramics, metalwork, jewelry, textiles, and manuscripts across five floors.
name: Museum of Islamic Art

excerpt: Walkers & joggers are regular sights at this 7-km-long, palm-lined promenade encircling Doha Bay.
detail_description: Doha Corniche is a picturesque 7-km-long promenade that encircles Doha Bay, offering stunning views of the Persian Gulf. Lined with palm trees and green parks, it's a popular spot for walkers and joggers. The area boasts a diverse culinary scene, with restaurants representing cuisines from all over the world. Visitors can enjoy coffee by the waterfront or dine after exploring nearby attractions like the Museum of Islamic Art and Msheireb Downtown Doha.
name: Doha Corniche

excerpt: Architecturally unique musuem with historical & natural history exhibits, including many artifacts.
detail_description: The National Museum of Qatar (NMoQ) is a visually stunning museum that showcases the history and culture of Qatar. The museum's unique architecture, designed by Jean Nouvel, resembles an intricate desert rose and seamlessly integrates the historic Palace of Sheikh Abdullah bin Jassim Al Thani. Visitors can explore immersive exhibitions that trace Qatar's evolution from a desert inhabited by Bedouin tribes to a global pearl-trading hub and a modern, oil-rich state.
name: National Museum of Qatar

excerpt: Large, tree-studded green space with a lake, fountains, playgrounds & nearby eateries.
detail_description: Aspire Park, the largest in the city at over 80 hectares, is a stunning green space featuring a lake, fountains, and playgrounds. Nestled behind the Villaggio and Hyatt Plaza, this expansive oasis offers a 1.6-kilometer jogging track and diverse aquatic life in its large lake.
name: Aspire Park
address: Aspire Zone, Aspire Park Running Trail, Doha, Qatar

detail_description: The Qatar National Library is a treasure trove of knowledge, boasting over 1 million books that document the history of Qatar and the Gulf Region. Established as the country's official national library in 2018, it has become an invaluable resource for residents. The library features a stunning glass ceiling reaching 72 feet high and offers various amenities including collaborative and individual learning spaces, children's and young adult collections, computer labs, performance areas, dining options, assistive technology facilities, and a writing center.
name: Qatar National Library
address: District of Freedom, Education City, Al Luqta St, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Italianate-themed shopping mall with luxury retail stores & a 150m-long indoor canal with gondolas.
detail_description: Villaggio Mall in Doha is a unique Italian-themed shopping destination that offers more than just luxury retail stores. Families with children will find it particularly appealing, as the mall features Gondolania Indoor Theme Park, the largest family entertainment center in Doha. This park includes a variety of attractions such as a Ferris wheel, bowling alley, bumper cars, roller coaster, go-kart racing, billiard tables, 4D theater, free-fall drop tower, and more.
name: Villaggio Mall

excerpt: Modern development, the first in Qatar to be available to foreigners on a Freehold basis.
detail_description: The Pearl Island, located in Qatar, is a modern development that offers freehold ownership to foreigners. It features luxury homes, parks, marinas, and glamorous resorts like The Four Seasons Resort and Residence. This man-made archipelago consists of 200 small artificial islands with golden sandy shores and upscale amenities such as design boutiques, global restaurants, beach clubs, and nightclubs.
name: The Pearl Island

excerpt: Islamic cultural center with a mosque, lectures & Arabic language classes, plus educational trips.
detail_description: Abdullah Bin Zaid Al Mahmoud Islamic Cultural Center, also known as Fanar Masjid, is a prominent landmark in Doha with its distinctive spiral tower. The center offers various initiatives to help people understand Qatari culture, the Arabic language, and Islam. Visitors can explore the mosque, attend English sermons on Fridays, and engage in discussions about Qatari lifestyle and faith.
name: Abdullah Bin Zaid Al Mahmoud Islamic Cultural Center (Fanar Masjid)

excerpt: Market dedicated to falconry, featuring trained birds & related equipment, such as hoods & jesses.
detail_description: The Souq Waqif Falcon Hospital is a unique market dedicated to falconry, offering trained birds and related equipment such as hoods and jesses. Located along Al Souq Street, it represents traditional practices of desert nomads and Qatari culture. Visitors can learn about the basics of falconry and its significance in Qatari culture. The souq also features a falcon hospital where visitors can observe fundamental procedures for treating and caring for these treasured birds.
name: Souq Waqif Falcon Hospital

excerpt: Contemporary museum with thousands of works by Arab artists, plus temporary exhibitions & events.
detail_description: Mathaf: Arab Museum of Modern Art, also known as Mathaf, is a contemporary museum located in Doha's Education City. Established in 2010, it features over 6,300 pieces of Arabian art dating from the 19th century to the present day. The museum is housed in a renovated building designed by French architect Jean-Francois Bodin. Under the patronage of H.E.
name: Mathaf: Arab Museum of Modern Art
address: Education City Student Center, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Museum in 4 historic, traditional homes with historical & cultural information & exhibits.
detail_description: Msheireb Museums, located in the heart of Doha's old downtown area, consists of four historic houses that have been meticulously restored to showcase Qatar's rich cultural heritage and history. Each house offers a unique perspective on Qatari life, using a combination of traditional exhibits and modern technology to bring the stories to life.
name: Msheireb Museums

excerpt: These 19th-century watchtowers next to an oasis are built out of coral stone & limestone.
detail_description: Barzan Towers, also known as the Umm Salal Mohammed Fort Towers, are 19th-century watchtowers located in the suburbs of Doha in Umm Salal Mohammed village. These towers were built with coral stone and limestone to serve as a lookout for approaching ships and protect local water sources. The architectural design is a rectangular building with three storeys and an external staircase, showcasing exceptional Arabian architectural style.
name: Barzan Towers

excerpt: Located within the city, this quaint beach features boating amenities & a children's play area.
detail_description: Katara Beach is a charming beach located within the city, offering boating amenities and a children's play area. The area has seen the emergence of night markets in various prime locations across Qatar, including Katara, where expats have introduced a variety of cuisines from around the world. This beautiful cultural village is a sought-after destination for visitors to Doha, featuring cafes, galleries, and a lovely promenade.
name: Katara Beach

excerpt: Prominent, urban park featuring a playground, cultural heritage center, shops & open green space.
detail_description: Al Bidda Park is a sprawling urban oasis in Doha, Qatar, spanning over 2 million square meters. It's the first pet-friendly park in the city and offers various public facilities, including underground parking for 6,000 cars. The park boasts a human maze, gymnasiums (including one for women), outdoor exercise equipment, playgrounds, an open-air theater seating 850 people, and tracks for bicycles, horses, and camels.
name: Al Bidda Park

detail_description: MIA Park is a serene oasis in Doha, offering stunning views of the Museum of Islamic Art and the Arabian Gulf. The park features lush green lawns, palm trees, and a picturesque promenade for leisurely strolls. The museum's collection showcases diverse Islamic art from three continents, spanning from the 7th to the 20th century. Visitors can also enjoy traditional dhows and public art along the corniche on their way to MIA Park.
name: MIA Park

excerpt: Msheireb Downtown Doha is a developing area with contemporary architecture, gleaming white mosques, and a cluster of history museums housed in elegant, Arabic-style mansions. Qatari family life is portrayed in Radwani House, while Bin Jalmood House has exhibitions on worldwide slavery. Eating options include global dining in high-end hotels, while the popular souvenir stalls and arcades of Souq Waqif are nearby.
detail_description: Msheireb Downtown Doha is an up-and-coming district characterized by modern design, striking white mosques, and a collection of historical museums located in stylish Arabic-inspired buildings. Radwani House offers insights into Qatari family traditions, while Bin Jalmood House showcases exhibitions on global slavery. Visitors can enjoy diverse dining experiences at upscale hotels and explore the nearby Souq Waqif for souvenir shopping and entertainment.
name: Msheireb Downtown Doha

detail_description: Doha Festival City is a massive shopping destination in the north of Doha, covering 600,000 square meters. It features over 400 brands, including luxury names like Dolce & Gabbana and Gucci. The mall also houses the first Harvey Nichols and IKEA outlets in the country.
name: Doha Festival City

excerpt: A 1920s military fort now serving as a museum with Qatari handicrafts, photos, paintings & more.
detail_description: Al Koot Fort, also known as Doha Fort, is a historical landmark situated in the heart of Souq Waqif. Originally built in 1927 to protect the area, it has been transformed into a captivating museum showcasing Qatari culture and history. The fort features exhibitions of traditional handicrafts, wooden decorations, fishing equipment, boats, and historical photographs.
name: Doha Fort/Al Koot Fort

detail_description: Imam Muhammad ibn Abd al-Wahhab Mosque, also known as the State Grand Mosque, is a magnificent structure in Doha that pays homage to traditional Islamic architecture while incorporating modern elements. The mosque boasts an impressive building with numerous domes and a blend of traditional Arabic and contemporary design. It covers a vast area on the ground floor and features classic Islamic architectural details both inside and out.
name: Imam Muhammad ibn Abd al-Wahhab Mosque

detail_description: Nestled within the vibrant Katara Cultural Village, the Arab Postal Stamps Museum is a hidden gem that opened its doors in 2010. This unique museum showcases an impressive collection of stamps from 22 Arab nations, each piece telling a story about the rich cultures and traditions of these countries. Visitors can marvel at stamps that span various themes and historical periods, with the oldest dating back to 1927 from Jordan.
name: Arab Postal Stamps Museum

detail_description: The Khalifa International Tennis and Squash Complex is a top-rated sports facility in the Middle East, offering 21 tennis courts and round-the-clock access for enthusiasts. Visitors can enjoy various recreational activities organized by the complex, making it an ideal destination for sports lovers. While booking a court comes with some limitations, the well-maintained facilities and opportunities to witness world-class events like the exxonmobile 2019 tournament featuring players like Djokovic make it a must-visit.
name: Khalifa International Tennis and Squash Complex
address: Al Majles Twaon Street, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Doha is the capital city and main financial hub of Qatar. Located on the Persian Gulf coast in the east of the country, north of Al Wakrah and south of Al Khor and Lusail, it is home to most of the country's population. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Doha, the capital city and main financial hub of Qatar, is located on the Persian Gulf coast. It is home to most of the country's population and boasts a unique architectural design in areas like Mushreib. The Mandarin Oriental Doha hotel offers a modern and fashionable stay while cleverly integrating Qatar's traditional style.
name: Doha

excerpt: Sculpture depicting an open oyster shell with running water; a popular photo stop on the Corniche.
detail_description: The Pearl Monument, located at the Doha Corniche in Qatar, is a significant tribute to the country's history of pearl diving. Depicting an open oyster shell with a large pearl inside, it symbolizes Qatar's rich maritime heritage. The monument stands as a reminder of the nation's past reliance on pearling before its oil industry boom.
name: The Pearl Monument

detail_description: If you're looking for a day full of energy and excitement, Angry Birds World Theme Park is the place to be. Located just 21 minutes north of downtown Doha, this amusement park offers a wide range of electric and water games that guarantee unmatched fun for visitors of all ages. From thrilling rides like Evolution and disco rides to the drop tower ride, there's something for everyone.
name: Angry Birds World Theme Park
address: Doha Festival City, Al Shamal Rd, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Modern, streamlined shopping complex with brand-name shops, plus restaurants & a movie theater.
detail_description: Lagoona Mall is a modern and stylish shopping complex located in the upscale West Bay area of Doha. It features a wide range of brand-name shops, restaurants, and even a movie theater. The mall is home to Fifty One East, one of Qatar's most luxurious multi-brand stores. With its convenient location about 25 minutes from Hamad International Airport, Lagoona Mall offers a diverse selection of local, regional, and international retail brands catering to various budgets.
name: Lagoona Mall

excerpt: Compact mosque featuring a colorful & intricately decorated tile exterior with gold accents.
detail_description: The Katara Mosque in Doha is a stunning architectural gem located at the heart of the Katara Cultural Village. The mosque features intricate and colorful tile exteriors with gold accents, inspired by architectural styles from various regions. Its outstanding minaret, mosaic tiles, inscriptions, and artistic handicrafts make it a must-see attraction. Visitors are impressed by the beautifully ornate exterior and welcoming interior of the mosque.
name: Katara Mosque

detail_description: Al Riwaq Gallery, situated near the Museum of Islamic Art, is a versatile art space that hosts workshops, lectures, and exhibitions. With a capacity to accommodate up to 400 people outdoors and 150 indoors (or 250 for standing events), it overlooks the MIA park. The museum's collection showcases Islamic art from various continents spanning over thirteen centuries. Additionally, Al Riwaq Gallery is located near the scenic Corniche promenade with its array of cultural attractions and stunning views.
name: Al Riwaq Gallery
address: Near Museum of Islamic Art, Doha, Qatar

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Katara Cultural Village of Doha, the Katara Art Center stands as a beacon for contemporary art enthusiasts and emerging artists alike. This dynamic institution spans over 1,000 square meters of gallery space dedicated to showcasing diverse artistic expressions. The center is not just about exhibitions; it actively fosters creativity through workshops, performances, and community events that engage people of all ages.
name: Katara Art Center
address: Katara Cultural Village, building 5, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Grand 18-hole desert golf course featuring lakes, lush greenery & a clubhouse with 3 restaurants.
detail_description: Doha Golf Club is a top golf destination in Qatar, offering an 18-hole championship course and a 9-hole track. Established in 1998, it has become a hub for golf enthusiasts and has hosted various championships. The club provides lessons for players looking to enhance their skills. Additionally, visitors can enjoy the clubhouse's three restaurants.
name: Doha Golf Club

excerpt: High-tech indoor amusement park with brightly lit kids' rides, interactive games & roller coasters.
detail_description: Doha Quest is an indoor amusement park in downtown Doha, offering over 30 rides and attractions. It stands out for its integration of technology, including simulators and virtual reality games. Divided into three themed sections inspired by Arabian history, modern technology, imagination, and gravity fun, the park caters to both children and adults. The EpiQ roller coaster is a must-try as it's known as the tallest indoor roller coaster globally.
name: Doha Quest
address: Oasis Gate 2, Al Khaleej, Doha, Qatar

detail_description: Experience the raw beauty of Qatar's desert with a trip to Desert Safari Doha Qatar, just a short drive from the city. As you venture into the dunes, you may encounter wild camels and even have the chance to interact with them under careful guidance. The harsh yet captivating landscape offers unique photo opportunities and a glimpse into traditional Bedouin life.
name: Desert safari doha qatar

excerpt: Landmark 40,000-seat open-air arena, built in 1976 & host to iconic international sporting events.
detail_description: Khalifa International Stadium, located in Doha, Qatar, is a renowned 40,000-seat open-air arena that has been hosting iconic international sporting events since its establishment in 1976. As the country prepares to host the 2022 FIFA World Cup, this stadium will take center stage as one of Qatar's premier football venues with a capacity for 68,000 spectators.
name: Khalifa International Stadium‎

excerpt: Vast mall offering regional & global brands, plus a movie house & an ice rink spread over 5 stories.
detail_description: City Center Doha mall, located in the diplomatic quarter of West Bay, has recently undergone a major renovation to comply with safety regulations. The mall boasts an array of regional and global brands spread across five stories, along with entertainment options such as a movie theater and an ice rink. Connected to three international hotels, City Center Doha offers a convenient retail and leisure destination for visitors.
name: City Center Doha mall

excerpt: Single-level retail center with international & local chain stores, a food court & movie theater.
detail_description: Landmark Mall is a single-level retail center featuring a variety of international and local chain stores, a food court, and a movie theater. It is located in Al Duhail and is popular among expats for its global brands such as GAP, H&M, and Zara.
name: Landmark Mall

detail_description: Al Wakrah Souq, located in the expanded fishing village of Al Wakrah, is where England's rivals, the USA, have booked their stay. This vibrant marketplace is situated just 10 miles south of Doha and offers a unique cultural experience for visitors.
name: Al Wakrah Souq

detail_description: The Museum of Illusions Doha is an engaging and educational attraction located in the heart of Qatar. It offers a fantastical world of illusions based on science, mathematics, biology, and psychology. Visitors can explore interactive exhibits and optical illusions that challenge perceptions and provide insight into how the brain processes visual information. This museum is perfect for family outings, group gatherings, or special occasions.
name: Museum of Illusions Doha
address: The Gate Mall, Omar Al Mukhtar St, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Hip arts space in a former fire station with trendy exhibits, workshops, films & events.
detail_description: The Fire Station Museum, formerly a Civil Defence Building housing Qatar's Fire Brigade, has been transformed into a vibrant arts space by Qatari architect Ibrahim Al Jeidah. The Garage Gallery within the museum showcases exhibitions by emerging local artists and hosts an artist-in-residence program to support talent development. The building's external walls feature murals commemorating significant events in Qatar's history.
name: Fire Station Museum
address: Fire Station, Mohammed Bin Thani, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Inspired by a minaret, this 7-sided artwork by the sea reflects Islamic culture & is 78 feet high.
detail_description: The sculpture, named "7 Sculpture by Richard Serra", is a large and unusual work of art located in a peaceful location. The sculpture is made up of seven steel plates that are a special spiritual symbol in Qatari and Islamic culture. Visitors can walk through the sculpture and look up at the sky from inside. The sculpture is a fantastic addition to the area and well worth the drive.
name: The 7 Sculpture By Richard Serra

excerpt: Brand-name stores, restaurants & a movie theater in opulent surrounds with a water fountain.
detail_description: Al Mirqab Mall is a luxurious shopping destination in Doha, Qatar, offering a blend of brand-name stores, restaurants, and entertainment options. Situated on one of the city's oldest shopping streets, the mall combines modern amenities with Qatari traditions. Its open-air feel is achieved through large glass windows and promenade entrances within air-conditioned spaces. The stunning architecture includes a glass roof that allows ample natural light to showcase the mall's design.
name: Al Mirqab Mall
address: Al Mirqab Al Jadeed St, Doha, Qatar

excerpt: Stylish mall with designer brands, a food court & water feature, plus a multiplex & kids' play area.
detail_description: Tawar Mall in Doha, Qatar is a popular shopping destination offering a wide range of retail, dining, and entertainment options. Situated in the bustling commercial and residential district of the city, this expansive mall features a modern design with elegant and distinctive elements. Spanning an impressive 300,958m2, it offers a luxurious shopping experience with designer brands and a variety of dining choices.
name: Tawar Mall

detail_description: Hotel Park in Doha is a true urban oasis with stunning views of the city's skyline, lush green spaces, and relaxing walkways. Located just 5 minutes from downtown, it offers a perfect escape from the city buzz. This popular destination is ideal for family picnics, bike rides, and enjoying the picturesque surroundings. Visitors can appreciate the city's efforts to introduce more green spaces by taking a break at Hotel Park amidst their sightseeing adventures.
name: Hotel Park

detail_description: BoxPark in Doha is a popular destination with its vibrant repurposed containers and stunning views, making it a great place to visit. The park offers a variety of restaurants and shops for leisurely shopping and relaxation. It's also an ideal spot for dog walking, featuring a beautiful view of a stadium, air-conditioned seating areas, and garden walking paths.
name: BoxPark
address: Doha box park, Next to halul restaurant, Qatar

detail_description: Located in the Katara area of Doha, Al Thuraya Planetarium offers an exciting and educational experience for visitors of all ages. The planetarium is named after the Thuraya cluster of stars, which translates to 'wealth' in Arabic. It features a full-dome digital system that projects images and videos of planets, along with 3D presentations and advanced technology synchronized with other systems worldwide. Inside the museum, interactive screens showcase information about famous Arab astronomers and historical astronomical tools.
name: Al Thuraya Planetarium
address: Katara Cultural Village،, Building 41, Doha, Qatar

detail_description: Qanat Quartier, located within The Pearl in Doha, is often considered the most picturesque area in the city. This vibrant neighborhood features colorful buildings set against an emerald green canal, creating a stunning backdrop for photography enthusiasts. Despite being part of a generally quiet suburb with many unoccupied apartments and shops, Qanat Quartier offers a lively and visually appealing atmosphere for visitors to enjoy.
name: Qanat Quartier

detail_description: Desert Safari Doha offers a variety of activities for families, including dhow cruises departing from the Museum of Islamic Arts. These traditional boats take you to an offshore island where you can swim in the Arabian Gulf or simply enjoy views of West Bay and the corniche while savoring a traditional Arabic BBQ.
name: Desert Safari Doha | Inland Sea Tours Qatar

detail_description: 21 High Street, opened in 2019, is a luxurious shopping destination that has quickly become a favorite among locals and visitors alike. Developed by Ali Bin Ali Holding, the Qatari company aimed to bring high-end international brands closer to home. The mall boasts an impressive lineup of luxury retailers such as Cartier and Galeries Lafayette. With multiple levels, it offers a seamless blend of retail therapy and culinary delights with its array of restaurants and cafes.
name: 21 High Street
address: 21 High Street Katara PB NO. 75, Doha, Qatar

detail_description: Poseidon Dive Center in Qatar offers an amazing experience for beginners and experienced divers alike. The instructors are highly praised for their patience, friendliness, and informative approach. They ensure a comfortable learning pace and prioritize the safety and confidence of their students. Despite any scheduling challenges, the team remains accommodating and dedicated to providing a great diving experience.
name: Poseidon Dive Center ,Qatar
address: Hilton Hotel ,Ground Floor, Diplomatic St, Doha, Qatar

detail_description: Al Fanar Masjid, also known as the Sheikh Abdulla Bin Zaid Al Mahmoud Islamic Cultural Centre, is a remarkable destination in Doha that beautifully blends spirituality and cultural education. This stunning mosque features an eye-catching minaret that spirals gracefully into the sky, while its interior reflects simplicity rooted in local traditions. The center serves as a hub for both residents and visitors, offering free Arabic classes and various exhibitions aimed at educating non-Muslims about Qatari culture and Islam.
name: AL FANAR MASJID
